<p>Here /dev/sdb is the USB device attached and &ldquo;pci-0000:00:14.0-usb-0:4.2:1.0-scsi-0:0:0:0&rdquo; file which represents the USB device describes that the USB device is connected from PCI bus to SCSI adapter.&ldquo;by-path&rdquo; is the pci path of the disk device. this device file name is created depending on the shortest physical path to the device.
&ldquo;/dev/sda&rdquo; the first SCSI drive on the first SCSI bus,/dev/sdb is the second SCSI drive and /dev/sdc is the third SCSI drive and so on.</p>
